          {
            "key": "usageNote-en",
            "note": "Best practice is to use the <a href=\"https://www.iso.org/standard/72482.html\">ISO 3166-1 code</a> but if this is inappropriate for the context, country names should be provided in a consistent manner to reduce ambiguity. For example, either write 'France' or 'FRA' consistently throughout the dataset and avoid mixing the two. The <a href=\"https://op.europa.eu/en/web/eu-vocabularies/dataset/-/resource?uri=http://publications.europa.eu/resource/dataset/country\">Country controlled vocabulary</a> from the Publications Office can be reused for this.",
